com.mumfrey.liteloader.api

Interface LiteAPI

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LiteLoaderCoreAPI, LiteLoaderCoreAPIClient

    public interface LiteAPI
    LiteLoader Extensible API - main Mod API Implementors of this class don't really do anything except provide instances of other classes which make up the API proper. Where possible, instance things as LATE as possible (eg. do not instance your CoreProviders in the constructor or init()) because it's possible to screw up the game startup if things get loaded out of order, in general it's best to instance things only at the earliest point in time at which they are needed.
    Author:
    Adam Mummery-Smith

        int getRevision()
        Get the revision number of this API. Unlike the version number, the revision number should only change when an incompatible change is made to the APIs interfaces, it is also used when a mod specifies an API dependency using the api@revision syntax
